obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3387)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3387&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Coast Guard Act, 1978.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 19th August, 1978, vide notification No. S.R.O. 10(E), dated 18th August, 1978, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3388)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 2, for "or a Sahayak Engineer" (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3388&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chief Law Officer" and "Law Officer" mean, respectively, the Chief Law Officer and a Law`
  line `Officer of the Coast Guard appointed under section 115;`
  line
  line `(b) "civil offence" means an offence which is triable by a criminal court;`
  line
  line `(c) "civil prison" means any jail or place used for the detention of any criminal prisoner under the`
  line `Prisons Act, 1894 (9 of 1894), or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(d) "Coast Guard" means the Coast Guard constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Coast Guard Court" means a court convened under section 64;`
  line
  line `(f) "Coast Guard custody" means the arrest or confinement of a member of the Coast Guard`
  line `according to rules;`
  line
  line `(g) "Commanding Officer", when used in any provision of this Act with reference to any unit or`
  line `ship of the Coast Guard, means the officer whose duty it is under the rules to discharge with respect`
  line `to that unit or ship, the functions of a Commanding Officer in regard to matters of the description`
  line `referred to in that provision;`
  line
  line `(h) "criminal court" means a court of ordinary criminal justice in any part of India;`
  line
  line `(i) "Deputy Inspector-General" means a Deputy Inspector-General of the Coast Guard appointed`
  line `under section 5;`
  line
  line `(j) "Director-General" means the Director-General of the Coast Guard appointed under section 5;`
  line
  line `(k) "enrolled person" means a subordinate officer, sailor or other person enrolled under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Inspector-General" means an Inspector-General of the Coast Guard appointed under`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(m) "maritime zones of India" means the territorial waters, the contiguous zone, the continental`
  line `shelf, the exclusive economic zone or any other maritime zone of India;`
  line
  line `(n) "member of the Coast Guard" means an officer, a subordinate officer, a sailor or other`
  line `enrolled person;`
  line
  line `(o) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(p) "offence" means any act or omission punishable under this Act and includes a civil offence;`
  line
  line `(q) "officer" means a person appointed or in pay as an officer of the Coast Guard, but does not`
  line `include a subordinate officer, sailor or other enrolled person;`
  line
  line `(r) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) "rule" means a rule made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) "sailor" means a member of the Coast Guard other than an officer, a subordinate officer or`
  line `other enrolled person;`
  line
  line `(u) "ship", except in the expression "on board a ship", means a Coast Guard vessel, and includes`
  line `any establishment or station belonging to, or under the control of, the Coast Guard whether within or`
  line `without India;`
  line
  line `(v) "skipper" means a subordinate officer in command of a ship;`
  line
  line `(w) "subordinate officer" means a person appointed or in pay as a Pradhan Adhikari, a Pradhan`
  line `Sahayak Engineer, an Uttam Adhikari, an Uttam Sahayak Engineer, an Adhikari ^1`
  line `[, a Sahayak`
  line `Engineer or a Pradhan Yantrik] of the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(x) "superior officer", when used in relation to a person subject to this Act, means any officer or`
  line `subordinate officer--`
  line
  line `(i) who is senior to that person under the rules; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is entitled under this Act or the rules to give a command to that person;`
  line
  line `(y) "territorial waters", "contiguous zone", "continental shelf" and "exclusive economic zone",`
  line `shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf,`
  line `Exclusive Economic Zone and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(z) all words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860) shall have the meanings assigned to them in that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3389)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Persons subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3389&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following persons shall be subject to this Act, wherever`
  line `they may be, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) officers;`
  line
  line `(b) subordinate officers and other persons enrolled under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) persons who have, by a general or special order of the Central Government, been required to`
  line `serve in a ship, to such extent and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(d) persons ordered to be received, or being passengers, on board any ship or aircraft of the Coast`
  line `Guard, to such extent and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person referred to in clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) shall remain so subject until he`
  line `retires, or he is discharged, released, removed or dismissed from the Coast Guard in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3390)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Coast Guard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3390&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an armed force of the Union called the`
  line `Coast Guard for ensuring the security of the maritime zones of India with a view to the protection of`
  line `maritime and other national interests in such zones.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Coast Guard shall be constituted in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed and the conditions of service of the members of the Coast Guard shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3391)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Control, direction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3391&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and control of the Coast`
  line `Guard shall vest in, and be exercised by, the Central Government and subject thereto, and to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules, the command and supervision of the Coast Guard shall vest in an`
  line `officer to be appointed by the Central Government as the Director-General of the Coast Guard.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director-General shall, in the discharge of his duties under this Act, be assisted by such`
  line `number of Inspectors-General, Deputy Inspectors-General, Commandant and such other officers as may`
  line `be appointed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3392)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Enrolment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3392&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons to be enrolled to the Coast Guard, the mode of enrolment and the`
  line `procedure for enrolment shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and the rules, every person who has, for a`
  line `continuous period of three months, been in receipt of pay as a person enrolled under this Act and borne on`
  line `the rolls of the Coast Guard shall be deemed to have been duly enrolled.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3393)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Liability for service outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3393&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Coast Guard shall be liable to serve in`
  line `any part of India as well as outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3394)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Oath of allegiance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3394&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Coast Guard shall, as soon as may be, after`
  line `appointment or enrolment to the Coast Guard, make and subscribe before his Commanding Officer or`
  line `other prescribed officer, an oath or affirmation in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3395)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Resignation and withdrawal from the post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3395&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No member of the Coast Guard shall be at`
  line liberty--
  line
  line `(a) to resign his appointment during the term of his engagement; or`
  line
  line `(b) to withdraw himself from all or any of the duties of his appointment,`
  line
  line `except with the previous permission in writing of the prescribed authority`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3396)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Tenure of service under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3396&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the Coast Guard shall hold office during`
  line `the pleasure of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3397)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Dismissal or removal by Central Government and by other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3397&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government may dismiss or remove from service any member of the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director-General or any Inspector-General may dismiss or remove from the Coast Guard`
  line `any person other than an officer;`
  line
  line `(c) any prescribed officer not below the rank of a Deputy Inspector-General may dismiss or`
  line `remove from the Coast Guard any person under his command other than an officer or a subordinate`
  line officer.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3398)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Certificate of termination of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3398&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `An enrolled person who retires, or is discharged,`
  line `released, removed or dismissed from the Coast Guard or permitted to resign therefrom, shall be furnished`
  line `by the officer, to whose command he is subject, with a certificate in the language which is the mother`
  line `tongue of such person and also in Hindi or English language setting forth--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority terminating his service;`
  line
  line `(b) the reasons for such termination ; and`
  line
  line `(c) the full period of his service in the Coast Guard.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3399)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Restrictions respecting right to form association, freedom of speech, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3399&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of`
  line `the Coast Guard shall, without the previous sanction in writing of the Central Government or of the`
  line `prescribed authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, or political`
  line `association; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation that is not recognised as part of the Coast Guard or is not of a purely social, recreational`
  line `or religious nature; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line `document except where such communication or publication is in the bona fide discharge of his duties`
  line `or is of a purely literary, artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--If any question arises whether any society, institution, association or organisation is of`
  line `a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) of this sub-section, the decision of the`
  line `Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Coast Guard shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any`
  line `demonstration organised by any body of persons for any political purposes or for such other purposes as`
  line `may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3400)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Duties and functions of Coast Guard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3400&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Coast Guard to protect by`
  line `such measures, as it thinks fit, the maritime and other national interests of India in the maritime zones of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the measures referred to`
  line `therein may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) ensuring the safety and protection of artificial islands, offshore terminals, installations and`
  line `other structures and devices in any maritime zone;`
  line
  line `(b) providing protection to fishermen including assistance to them at sea while in distress;`
  line
  line `(c) taking such measures as are necessary to preserve and protect the maritime environment and`
  line `to prevent and control marine pollution;`
  line
  line `(d) assisting the customs and other authorities in anti-smuggling operations;`
  line
  line `(e) enforcing the provisions of such enactments as are for the time being in force in the maritime`
  line `zones; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other matters, including measures for the safety of life and property at sea and collection`
  line `of scientific data, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Coast Guard shall perform its functions under this section in accordance with, and subject to`
  line `such rules as may be prescribed and such rules may, in particular, make provisions for ensuring that the`
  line `Coast Guard functions in close liaison with Union agencies, institutions and authorities so as to avoid`
  line `duplication of effort.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3401)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Correspondence, etc., with offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3401&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, who,--`
  line
  line `(a) treacherously holds correspondence with, or communicates intelligence to, an offender; or`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully fails to make known to the proper authorities any information he may have received`
  line `from an offender; or`
  line
  line `(c) assists the offender in any manner; or`
  line
  line `(d) having been captured by an offender, voluntarily serves with or aids him,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "offender" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) all armed mutineers, armed rebels, armed rioters, pirates and any person in arms against`
  line `whom it is the duty of any person subject to this Act to take action ; and`
  line
  line `(b) any person or persons engaged in smuggling, unlawful exploration or exploitation or any`
  line `other unlawful activity in the maritime zones of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3402)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Deserting post and neglect of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3402&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, who,--`
  line
  line `(a) deserts his post; or`
  line
  line `(b) sleeps upon his watch; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails to perform, or negligently performs, the duty imposed on him; or`
  line
  line `(d) wilfully conceals any words, practice or design tending to the hindrance of the Coast Guard,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3403)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Mutiny.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3403&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) begins, incites, causes or conspires with any other person to cause any mutiny in the Coast`
  line `Guard or in the military, naval or air forces of India or any forces co-operating therewith; or`
  line
  line `(b) joins in any such mutiny; or`
  line
  line `(c) being present at any such mutiny, does not use his utmost endeavours to suppress the same; or`
  line
  line `(d) knowing or having reason to believe in the existence of any such mutiny, or of any intention`
  line `to mutiny or of any such conspiracy, does not, without delay, give information thereof to his`
  line `Commanding Officer or other superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(e) endeavours to seduce any person in the Coast Guard or in the military, naval or air forces of`
  line `India or any forces co-operating therewith from his duty or allegiance to the Union,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer death or such less punishment as is in this`
  line `Act mentioned:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sentence of death awarded under this section shall not be carried out unless it is`
  line `confirmed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3404)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Persons on board ship or aircraft seducing Coast Guard personnel from allegiance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3404&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person not otherwise subject to this Act who, being on board any ship or aircraft belonging to or in the`
  line `service of the Coast Guard endeavours to seduce any person subject to this Act from his allegiance to the`
  line `Constitution or loyalty to the State or duty to his superior officers shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard`
  line `Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3405)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Striking or threatening superior officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3405&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) uses criminal force to or assaults his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses threatening language to such officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) uses insubordinate language to such officer; or`
  line
  line `(d) behaves with contempt to such officer,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of offences specified in clauses (c) and (d), the imprisonment shall not`
  line `exceed five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3406)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Disobedience to superior officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3406&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who disobeys in such`
  line `manner as to show a wilful defiance of authority any lawful command given personally by his superior`
  line `officer in the execution of his office whether the same is given orally, or in writing or by signal or`
  line `otherwise, shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who disobeys any lawful command given by his superior officer,`
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3407)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Ill-treating subordinates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3407&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who uses criminal force to or`
  line `otherwise ill-treats any other person subject to this Act, being his subordinate in rank or position, shall, on`
  line `conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3408)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Quarrelling, fighting and disorderly behaviour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3408&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, who,--`
  line
  line `(a) quarrels, fights with or strikes any other person, whether such person is or is not subject to`
  line `this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses reproachful or provoking speeches or gestures tending to make a quarrel or`
  line `disturbance; or`
  line
  line `(c) behaves in a disorderly manner,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3409)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Certain forms of disgraceful conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3409&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) is guilty of any disgraceful conduct of a cruel, indecent or unnatural kind; or`
  line
  line `(b) malingers, or feigns, or produces disease or infirmity in himself or intentionally delays his`
  line `cure or aggravates his disease or infirmity; or`
  line
  line `(c) with intent to render himself or any other person unfit for service, voluntarily causes hurt to`
  line `himself or that person,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3410)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Drunkenness.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3410&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act, who is guilty of drunkenness shall, on`
  line `conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), a person shall be deemed to be guilty of drunkenness if,`
  line `owing to the influence of alcohol or any drug whether alone or in combination with any other`
  line `circumstances, he is unfit to be entrusted with his duty or with any duty which he may be called upon to`
  line `perform or behaves in a disorderly manner or in a manner likely to bring discredit to the Coast Guard.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3411)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Desertion and aiding desertion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3411&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act, who absents himself from`
  line `his ship or from the place where his duty requires him to be, with an intention of not returning to such`
  line `ship or place, or who, at any time and under any circumstances when absent from his ship or place of duty`
  line `does any act which shows that he has an intention of not returning to such ship or place is said to desert.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) Every person who deserts or attempts to desert the Coast Guard shall, on conviction by a Coast`
  line `Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned and in every such case he shall forfeit,--`
  line
  line `(a) all pay, salvage, prize money and allowances that have been earned by him;`
  line
  line `(b) pension and gratuity, medals and decorations that have been granted to him; and`
  line
  line `(c) all clothes and effects which he may have left on board the ship or the place from which he`
  line deserted,
  line
  line `unless the Tribunal by which he is tried or the Central Government or the Director-General otherwise`
  line directs.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, all pay, salvage, prize money and allowances`
  line `shall be deemed to have been earned by a person when such pay, salvage, prize money and allowances`
  line `have become due but have not been paid to him.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any person subject to this Act, who knowingly harbours any such deserter, shall, on conviction by`
  line `a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or such`
  line `less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3412)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Breaking out of ship and absence without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3412&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, who without`
  line `being guilty of desertion improperly leaves his ship or place of duty or is absent without leave shall, on`
  line `conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned, and shall also be punished by such mulcts of`
  line `pay and allowances as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (3413)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Losing ship or aircraft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3413&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who wilfully loses, strands or`
  line `hazards or suffers to be lost stranded or hazarded any ship belonging to or in the service of the Coast`
  line `Guard, or loses or suffers to be lost any aircraft belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard shall, on`
  line `conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act, who negligently or by any default loses, strands or hazards or`
  line `suffers to be lost, stranded or hazarded any ship belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard, or loses`
  line `or suffers to be lost any aircraft belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard shall, on conviction by a`
  line `Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or such`
  line `less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (3414)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Dangerous unauthorised flying.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3414&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who is guilty of any act or`
  line `neglect in flying or in the use of any aircraft belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard, or in`
  line `relation to any such aircraft or aircraft material, which causes or is likely to cause loss of life or bodily`
  line `injury to any person shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he acts wilfully or with wilful neglect, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years`
  line `or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (3415)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Inaccurate certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3415&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who signs any certificate in relation to an`
  line `aircraft belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard or to any material thereof without ensuring its`
  line `accuracy shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (3416)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Low flying and annoyance by flying.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3416&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, being the pilot of an`
  line `aircraft belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard, who--`
  line
  line `(a) flies it at a height lower than the minimum height authorised by his Commanding Officer`
  line `except while taking off or landing; or`
  line
  line `(b) flies it so as to cause or likely to cause unnecessary annoyance to any person,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (3417)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Disobedience of lawful command of captain of an aircraft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3417&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act,`
  line `who while he is in an aircraft belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard, disobeys any lawful`
  line `command given by the captain of the aircraft whether such captain is subject to this Act or not, in relation`
  line `to all matters relating to flying or handling of the aircraft or affecting the safety thereof, shall, on`
  line `conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (3418)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `False accusations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3418&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, who commits any of the following offences,`
  line `that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes a false accusation against any person subject to this Act, knowing or having reason to`
  line `believe such accusation to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) in making a complaint against any person subject to this Act makes any statement affecting`
  line `the character of such person, knowing or having reason to believe such statement to be false or`
  line `knowingly or wilfully suppresses any material facts,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (3419)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Falsifying official documents and false declarations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3419&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any report, return, list, certificate, book or other document made or signed by him, or of the`
  line `contents of which it is his duty to ascertain the accuracy, knowingly makes, or is privy to the making`
  line `of, any false or fraudulent statement; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any document of the description mentioned in clause (a) knowingly makes, or is privy to`
  line `the making of, any omission, with intent to defraud; or`
  line
  line `(c) knowingly and with intent to injure any person, or knowingly and with intent to defraud,`
  line `suppresses, defaces, alters or makes away with any document which it is his duty to preserve or`
  line `produce; or`
  line
  line `(d) where it is his official duty to make a declaration respecting any matter, knowingly makes a`
  line `false declaration; or`
  line
  line `(e) obtains for himself, or for any other person, any pension, allowance or other advantage or`
  line `privilege by a statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false, or does not`
  line `believe to be true, or by making or using a false entry in any book or record, or by making any`
  line `document containing a false statement, or by omitting to make a true entry or document containing a`
  line `true statement,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (3420)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Offences in respect of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3420&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) commits theft of any property belonging to the Government or to any Coast Guard mess, or`
  line `institution, or to any person subject to this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) dishonestly misappropriates or converts to his own use any such property; or`
  line
  line `(c) commits criminal breach of trust in respect of any such property; or`
  line
  line `(d) dishonestly receives or retains any such property in respect of which any of the offences under`
  line `clauses (a), (b) and (c) has been committed, knowing or having reason to believe the commission of`
  line `such offence; or`
  line
  line `(e) wilfully destroys or damages any property of the Government entrusted to him; or`
  line
  line `(f) does any other thing with intent to defraud or to cause wrongful gain to one person or`
  line `wrongful loss to another person,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (3421)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Damage to property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3421&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act, who commits any act which causes`
  line `damage to, or destruction of, any property of the Government shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard`
  line `Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (3422)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Taking unauthorised goods on board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3422&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every officer or subordinate officer in command of any`
  line `ship belonging to or in the service of the Coast Guard who receives on board or permits to be received on`
  line `board such ship, any goods or merchandise whatsoever other than for the sole use of the ship or persons`
  line `belonging to the ship, except goods and merchandise on board any ship which may be ship-wrecked or in`
  line `imminent danger either on the high seas or in some port, creek or harbour for the purpose of preserving`
  line `them for their proper owners, or except such goods or merchandise as he may, at any time be ordered to`
  line `take or receive on board by order of the Central Government or his superior officer, shall, on conviction`
  line `by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer dismissal from the Coast Guard or such less punishment as is`
  line `in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (3423)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Offences in respect of papers relating to vessel, craft or aircraft taken into custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3423&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) All`
  line `the papers, charter parties, bills of lading, passports and other documents that shall be taken, seized or`
  line `found on board any vessel, craft or aircraft taken into custody by the Coast Guard shall be duly preserved`
  line `and the Commanding Officer or skipper shall send the same to his immediate superior.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Commanding Officer or skipper who fails to send the documents as required under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer dismissal from the Coast`
  line `Guard or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (3424)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Offences in respect of vessel, craft or aircraft taken into custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3424&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) takes out without proper authority from any vessel, craft or aircraft taken into custody, any`
  line `money or goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) pillages, beats or ill-treats persons on board the said vessel, craft or aircraft; or`
  line
  line `(c) breaks bulk on board any such vessel, craft or aircraft with intent dishonestly to`
  line `misappropriate anything therein or belonging thereto,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (3425)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Unlawful taking of ransom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3425&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Every Commanding Officer or skipper of a ship who,--`
  line
  line `(a) unlawfully agrees with any person for the ransoming of any vessel, craft, aircraft, goods or`
  line `things taken into custody by the Coast Guard; or`
  line
  line `(b) in pursuance of any unlawful agreement for ransoming or otherwise by collusion actually`
  line `quits or restores any vessel, craft, aircraft, goods or things taken into custody by the Coast Guard,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (3426)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Offences relating to Coast Guard Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3426&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) being duly summoned or ordered to attend as a witness before a Coast Guard Court, wilfully`
  line `or without reasonable excuse, makes default in attending; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses to take an oath or make an affirmation legally required by a Coast Guard Court to be`
  line `taken or made; or`
  line
  line `(c) refuses to produce or deliver any document in his power or control legally required by a Coast`
  line `Guard Court to be produced or delivered by him; or`
  line
  line `(d) refuses, when a witness, to answer any question which he is by law bound to answer; or`
  line
  line `(e) is guilty of contempt of a Coast Guard Court by using insulting or threatening language, or by`
  line `causing any interruption or disturbance in the proceedings of such Court,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (3427)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Escape from custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3427&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who, being in lawful custody, escapes or`
  line `attempts to escape, shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (3428)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Violation of the Act, rules and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3428&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who neglects to obey, or`
  line `contravenes any provision of this Act or any rule or any order issued by any lawful authority under this`
  line `Act, shall, if no other punishment is provided in this Act for such neglect or contravention, on conviction`
  line `by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or`
  line `such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (3429)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `False answers on enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3429&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Any person having become subject to this Act who is discovered`
  line `to have made at the time of enrolment, a wilfully false answer to any question set forth in the prescribed`
  line `form of enrolment which has been put to him by the enrolling officer before whom he appears for the`
  line `purpose of being enrolled, shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (3430)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Offences against good order and discipline.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3430&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who is guilty of`
  line `any act or omission or disorder or neglect, which, though not specified in this Act, is prejudicial to good`
  line `order and discipline of the Coast Guard shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, be liable to suffer`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or such less punishment as is in this Act`
  line mentioned.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (3431)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title Attempt.
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3431&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who attempts to commit any of the offences specified`
  line `in sections 15 to 44 (both inclusive) and in such attempt does any act towards the commission of the`
  line `offence shall, on conviction by a Coast Guard Court, where no express provision is made by this Act for`
  line `the punishment of such attempt, be liable,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence attempted to be committed is punishable with death, to suffer imprisonment for`
  line `a term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the offence attempted to be committed is punishable with imprisonment, to suffer`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one-half of the longest term provided for that offence`
  line `or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (3432)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Abetment of offences that have been committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3432&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who abets`
  line `the commission of any of the offences specified in sections 15 to 44 (both inclusive), shall, on conviction`
  line `by a Coast Guard Court, if the act abetted is committed in consequence of the abetment and no express`
  line `provision is made by this Act for the punishment of such abetment, be liable to suffer imprisonment`
  line `provided for that offence or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (3433)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Abetment of offence punishable with death and not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3433&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act, who abets the commission of an offence punishable with death under section 17 shall, on conviction`
  line `by a Coast Guard Court, if that offence be not committed in consequence of that abetment, be liable to`
  line `suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this`
  line `Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (3434)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Abetment of offences punishable with imprisonment and not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3434&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act, who abets the commission of an offence punishable with death under section 17 shall, on conviction`
  line `by a Coast Guard Court, if that offence be not committed in consequence of that abetment, be liable to`
  line `suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this`
  line `Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (3435)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Civil offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3435&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 50, any person subject to this Act who at any`
  line `place in, or beyond, India commits any civil offence shall be deemed to be guilty of an offence against`
  line `this Act and, if charged therewith under this section shall be liable to be tried by a Coast Guard Court,`
  line `and, on conviction, be punishable as follows, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence is one which would be punishable under any law in force in India with death, he`
  line `shall be liable to suffer any punishment, assigned for the offence, by the aforesaid law or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, he shall be liable to suffer any punishment, assigned for the offence by the`
  line `law in force in India, or imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (3436)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Civil offences not triable by a Coast Guard Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3436&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `A person subject to this Act who commits`
  line `an offence of murder or of culpable homicide not amounting to murder against, or of rape in relation to, a`
  line `person not subject to this Act shall not be deemed to be guilty of an offence against this Act and shall not`
  line `be tried by a Coast Guard Court, unless he commits any of the said offences,--`
  line
  line `(a) at any place outside India; or`
  line
  line `(b) at any place specified by the Central Government by notification in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (3437)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Period of limitation for trial of offences under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3437&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person unless he is an offender`
  line `who has avoided apprehension or escaped arrest or committed the offence of desertion or of giving false`
  line `entry on enrolment or the offence of mutiny shall be tried or punished in pursuance of this Act for any`
  line `offence committed by him unless such trial commences ^1`
  line `[within a period of three years from the`
  line `commission of such offence and such period shall commence,--`
  line
  line `(a) on the date of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the commission of the offence was not known to the person aggrieved by the offence or`
  line `to the authority competent to initiate action, the first day on which such offence comes to the`
  line `knowledge of such person or authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) where it is not known by whom the offence was committed, on the first day on which the`
  line `identity of the offender becomes known to the person aggrieved by the offence or to the authority`
  line `competent to initiate action,`
  line
  line `whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, in the computation of the period of time`
  line `mentioned in this sub-section, any time spent by such person, as a prisoner of war in the enemy territory,`
  line `or in evading arrest, after the commission of the offence, shall be excluded].`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(1A) Where a proceeding in respect of an offence has been stayed by an injunction or an order of a`
  line `court, then, in computing the period of limitation under this section, the period of the continuance of the`
  line `injunction or order, the day on which it was issued or made, and the day on which it was withdrawn shall`
  line `be excluded.]`
  line
  line `(2) No trial for an offence of desertion or of giving false entry on enrolment shall be commenced if`
  line `the person in question, not being an officer, has subsequent to the commission of the offence served`
  line `continuously in an exemplary manner for not less than three years in the Coast Guard.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 4, for "within three years from the commission of such offence" (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (3438)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Trial, etc., of a person who ceases to be subject to the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 5, for "within six months after he has ceased to be subject of this Act" (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3438&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this`
  line `Act had been committed by any person while subject to this Act, and such person has since the`
  line `commission of the offence ceased to be subject to this Act, he may be taken into and kept in the Coast`
  line `Guard custody, and tried and punished for such offence as if he had continued to be so subject.`
  line
  line `(2) No such person shall be tried for an offence, unless his trial commences ^1`
  line `[within a period of two`
  line `years after he has ceased to be subject to this Act; and in computing such period, the time during which`
  line `such person has avoided arrest by absconding or concealing himself or where a proceeding in respect of`
  line `an offence has been stayed by an injunction or order, the period of the continuance of the injunction or`
  line `order, the day on which it was issued or made and the day on which it was withdrawn, shall be excluded]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to the trial of any such person for an`
  line `offence of mutiny or desertion.`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (3439)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Punishments awardable by Coast Guard Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3439&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Punishments may be inflicted in respect`
  line `of offences committed by persons subject to this Act and convicted by Coast Guard Courts according to`
  line `the scale following, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) death;`
  line
  line `(b) imprisonment which may be for the term of life or any other lesser term;`
  line
  line `(c) dismissal from the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(d) detention in Coast Guard custody for a period not exceeding two years;`
  line
  line `(e) reduction to the ranks or to a lower rank in the case of sailors;`
  line
  line `(f) forfeiture of seniority of rank, forfeiture of all or any part of the service for the purpose of`
  line promotion;
  line
  line `(g) forfeiture of service for the purpose of increased pay, pension or any other prescribed purpose;`
  line
  line `(h) fine, in respect of civil offences;`
  line
  line `(i) mulcts of pay and allowances;`
  line
  line `(j) severe reprimand or reprimand except in the case of persons below the rank of an Uttam Navik`
  line `or Uttam Yantrik.`
  line
  line `(2) Each of the punishments specified in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be inferior in degree to`
  line `every punishment preceding it in the above scale.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (3440)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Alternative punishments awardable by Coast Guard Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3440&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, a Coast Guard Court may, on convicting a person subject to this Act of any of the offences`
  line `specified in sections 15 to 48 (both inclusive) award either the particular punishment with which the`
  line `offence is stated in the said sections to be punishable, or in lieu thereof, any one of the punishments lower`
  line `in the scale set out in section 53 regard being had to the nature and degree of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (3441)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Combination of punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3441&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 58, a sentence of a Coast`
  line `Guard Court may award in addition to, or without any one other punishment, the punishment specified`
  line `in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 53 and any one or more of the punishments specified in`
  line `clauses (e) to (j) (both inclusive) of that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (3442)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Punishments otherwise than by Coast Guard Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3442&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Punishments may also be inflicted in`
  line `respect of offences committed by persons subject to this Act without the intervention of a Coast Guard`
  line `Court in the manner stated in section 57 ^1`
  line `[or section 57A].`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (3443)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Minor punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3443&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 58, a Commanding Officer or such`
  line `other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government, specified by the Director-General may, in`
  line `the prescribed manner, proceed against a person subject to this Act, otherwise than as an officer, who is`
  line `charged with an offence under this Act and award such person, to the extent prescribed, one or more of`
  line `the following punishments, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) imprisonment for a period not exceeding three months;`
  line
  line `(b) dismissal from the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(c) detention in Coast Guard custody for a period not exceeding three months;`
  line
  line `(d) reduction to the ranks or to a lower rank in the case of sailors;`
  line
  line `(e) fine, in respect of civil offences;`
  line
  line `(f) mulcts of pay and allowances;`
  line
  line `(g) deprivation of good conduct badges;`
  line
  line `(h) reprimand;`
  line
  line `(i) extra work and drill for a period not exceeding fourteen days in the case of persons below the`
  line `rank of an Uttam Navik or Uttam Yantrik;`
  line
  line `(j) stoppage of leave for a period not exceeding sixty days;`
  line
  line `(k) admonition:`
  line
  line `Provided that no punishment specified in clauses (a) to (d) (both inclusive) shall be inflicted,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a subordinate officer, unless it is approved by an officer not below the rank of`
  line `an Inspector-General; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of others, unless it is approved by an officer not below the rank of a Deputy`
  line Inspector-General.
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57_a:
  sectionId (3444)
  sectionNo 57A
  orderNo 58
  title `Punishment for officers below the rank of Commandant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 7 (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3444&sectionno=57A&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_57_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[57A. Punishment for officers below the rank of Commandant.--The Director-General or an`
  line `officer not below the rank of Deputy Inspector-General who is appointed as Commander of a region or`
  line `such other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government, specified by the Director-General,`
  line `may in the prescribed manner proceed against an officer below the rank of Commandant, who is charged`
  line `with an offence under this Act and award such person one or more of the following punishments, that is`
  line `to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) forfeiture of seniority of rank or in the case of any of them whose promotion depends upon`
  line `length of service, forfeiture of service for the purpose of promotion, for a period not exceeding twelve`
  line `months, but subject to the right of the accused, previous to the award, to elect to be tried by a Coast`
  line `Guard Court;`
  line
  line `(b) forfeiture of seniority of rank, or in the case of any of them whose promotion depends upon`
  line `length of service, forfeiture of service for the purpose of promotion for a period not exceeding six`
  line `months, but subject to the right of the accused, previous to the award, to elect to be tried by a Coast`
  line `Guard Court;`
  line
  line `(c) mulcts of pay and allowances;`
  line
  line `(d) severe reprimand:`
  line
  line `Provided that no punishment specified in clause (a) shall be inflicted by an officer other that the`
  line `Director-General:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no punishment specified in clause (b) shall be inflicted by an officer below the`
  line `rank of Deputy Inspector-General who is appointed as the Commander of a region.]`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (3445)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 59
  title `Provisions as to award of punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 8 (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3445&sectionno=58&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The punishments that may be inflicted under this`
  line `Act shall be awarded in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) A sentence of imprisonment under this Act shall in all cases be accompanied by a sentence of`
  line dismissal.
  line
  line `(3) A sentence of imprisonment may be rigorous or simple or partly rigorous and partly simple.`
  line
  line `(4) No officer shall be subject to detention for any offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) No subordinate officer shall be sentenced to detention except for desertion.`
  line
  line `(6) A sentence of detention shall not be accompanied by a sentence of dismissal from the Coast`
  line Guard.
  line
  line `(7) A sentence of detention for a period exceeding fourteen days shall in all cases be accompanied by`
  line `stoppage of pay and allowances during the period of detention.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(8) Where mulcts of pay and allowances are awarded for absence without leave, the absence shall be`
  line `treated as regularised for all purposes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (3446)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 60
  title `Custody of offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3446&sectionno=59&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who is charged with an offence may`
  line `be taken into Coast Guard custody, under the order of any superior officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an officer may order into Coast Guard`
  line `custody any other officer engaged in a quarrel, affray or disorder, though such other officer may be of a`
  line `higher rank.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (3447)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 61
  title `Duty of Commanding Officer in regard to detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3447&sectionno=60&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every`
  line `Commanding Officer to take care that a person under his command when charged with an offence is not`
  line `detained in custody for more than forty-eight hours after the committal of such person into custody is`
  line `reported to him, without the charge being investigated, unless investigation within that period seems to`
  line `him to be impracticable having regard to the public service.`
  line
  line `(2) The case of every person being detained in custody beyond a period of forty-eight hours, and the`
  line `reasons therefor, shall be reported by the Commanding Officer to the Deputy Inspector-General under`
  line `whom he is serving or such other officer to whom an application may be made to convene a Coast Guard`
  line `Court for the trial of the person charged.`
  line
  line `(3) In reckoning the period of forty-eight hours specified in sub-section (1), Sundays and other public`
  line `holidays shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may make rules providing for the`
  line `manner in which and the period for which any person subject to this Act may be taken into and detained`
  line `in Coast Guard custody, pending the trial by any competent authority for any offence committed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (3448)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 62
  title `Arrest by civil authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3448&sectionno=61&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person subject to this Act, who is accused of an`
  line `offence under this Act, is within the jurisdiction of any Magistrate or police officer, such Magistrate or`
  line `police officer shall aid in the apprehension and delivery to Coast Guard custody of such person upon`
  line `receipt of a written application to that effect signed by his Commanding Officer or an officer authorised`
  line `by the Commanding Officer in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (3449)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 63
  title `Capture of deserters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3449&sectionno=62&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any person subject to this Act deserts, the Commanding`
  line `Officer of the unit or ship to which he belongs, shall give information of the desertion to such civil`
  line `authorities as, in his opinion, may be able to afford assistance towards the capture of the deserter; and`
  line `such authorities shall thereupon take steps for the apprehension of the said deserter in like manner as if he`
  line `was a person for whose apprehension a warrant had been issued by a Magistrate, and shall deliver the`
  line `deserter, when apprehended, into Coast Guard custody.`
  line
  line `(2) Any police officer may arrest without warrant any person reasonably believed to be subject to this`
  line `Act, and to be a deserter or to be travelling without authority, and shall bring him without delay before the`
  line `nearest Magistrate, to be dealt with according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (3450)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 64
  title `Coast Guard police officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3450&sectionno=63&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General or any prescribed officer may appoint`
  line `persons for discharging the functions specified in sub-sections (2) and (3).`
  line
  line `(2) The duties of a person appointed under sub-section (1), are to take charge of persons confined for`
  line `any offence, to preserve good order and discipline and to prevent breaches of the same by persons serving`
  line `in, or attached to, the Coast Guard.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 59, a person appointed under sub-section (1) may,`
  line `at any time, arrest and detain for trial any person subject to this Act who commits, or is charged with, an`
  line `offence, and may also carry into effect any punishment to be inflicted in pursuance of a sentence awarded`
  line `by a Coast Guard Court or by an officer exercising authority under section 57 but shall not inflict any`
  line `punishment on his own authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no officer shall be so arrested or detained otherwise than on the order of another officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (3451)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power to convene a Coast Guard Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3451&sectionno=64&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Coast Guard Court may be convened by the`
  line `Central Government or the Director-General or by any officer empowered in this behalf by warrant of the`
  line `Director-General (hereafter in this Act referred to as the convening authority).`
  line
  line `(2) A warrant issued under sub-section (1) may contain such restrictions, reservations or conditions as`
  line `the Director-General may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (3452)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 66
  title `Composition of Coast Guard Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3452&sectionno=65&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Coast Guard Court shall consist of not less than`
  line `five officers each of whom has held the post of Assistant Commandant for not less than three years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section "Assistant Commandant" includes any post of a`
  line `higher rank and any post declared by the Central Government by notification to be an equivalent post as`
  line `also any post higher in rank than the post so declared.`
  line
  line `(2) At every Coast Guard Court, the senior member shall be the presiding officer.`
  line
  line `(3) A Coast Guard Court shall not be duly constituted unless the members thereof are drawn from at`
  line `least two ships.`
  line
  line `(4) No Coast Guard Court for the trial of an officer shall be duly constituted unless the presiding`
  line `officer and at least two members of the court are of the same rank as the accused or of a higher rank.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (3453)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 67
  title `Dissolution of a Coast Guard Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3453&sectionno=66&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a Coast Guard Court after the commencement of a`
  line `trial is reduced below the minimum number of officers required by this Act, it shall be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on account of the illness of the Law Officer or of the accused before the finding, it is`
  line `impossible to continue the trial, a Coast Guard Court shall be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(3) The convening authority of a Coast Guard Court may dissolve the same if it considers that the`
  line `exigencies of the service or necessities of discipline render it impossible or inexpedient to continue the`
  line `said Coast Guard Court.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a Coast Guard Court is dissolved under this section, the accused may be tried again.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (3454)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 68
  title `Powers of a Coast Guard Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3454&sectionno=67&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Every Coast Guard Court shall have the power to try any`
  line `person subject to this Act for any offence punishable thereunder and to pass any sentence authorised`
  line thereby.
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (3455)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 69
  title `Prohibition of second trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3455&sectionno=68&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to this Act has been acquitted or`
  line `convicted of an offence by a Coast Guard Court or by a criminal court or has been dealt with under`
  line `section 57, he shall not be liable to be tried again for the same offence by a Coast Guard Court or dealt`
  line `with under the said section.`
  line
  line `(2) When any person, subject to this Act, has been acquitted or convicted of an offence by a Coast`
  line `Guard Court or has been dealt with under section 57, he shall not be liable to be tried again by a criminal`
  line `court for the same offence or on the same facts.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (3456)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 70
  title `Application of Act during term of sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3456&sectionno=69&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person subject to this Act is`
  line `sentenced by a Coast Guard Court to imprisonment, this Act shall apply to him during the term of his`
  line `sentence, though he is dismissed from the Coast Guard, or has otherwise ceased to be subject to this Act,`
  line `and he may be kept, removed, imprisoned and punished as if he continued to be subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) When a person subject to this Act is sentenced by a Coast Guard Court to death, this Act shall`
  line `apply to him till the sentence is carried out.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (3457)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 71
  title `Place of trial.`
  content `A Coast Guard Court may be held on shore or afloat.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3457&sectionno=70&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (3458)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 72
  title `Choice between criminal court and Coast Guard Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3458&sectionno=71&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `When a criminal court and a`
  line `Coast Guard Court have each jurisdiction in respect of an offence, it shall be in the discretion of the`
  line `Director-General or the Inspector-General or the Deputy Inspector-General within whose command the`
  line `accused person is serving or such other officer as may be prescribed, to decide before which court the`
  line `proceedings shall be instituted, and, if that officer decides that they shall be instituted before a Coast`
  line `Guard Court, to direct that the accused person shall be detained in Coast Guard custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (3459)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power of criminal court to require delivery of an offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3459&sectionno=72&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a criminal court having`
  line `jurisdiction is of opinion that proceedings shall be instituted before itself in respect of any alleged`
  line `offence, it may, by written notice, require the officer referred to in section 71 at his option either to`
  line `deliver over the offender to the nearest Magistrate to be proceeded against according to law, or to`
  line `postpone proceedings, pending a reference to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In every such case, the said officer shall either deliver over the offender in compliance with the`
  line `requisition, or shall forthwith refer the question as to the court before which the proceedings are to be`
  line `instituted, for the determination of the Central Government whose order upon such reference shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (3460)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 74
  title `Law Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3460&sectionno=73&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Every Coast Guard Court shall be attended by a Law Officer, or if no such officer`
  line `is available, an officer approved by the Chief Law Officer or a Law Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (3461)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 75
  title Challenges.
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3461&sectionno=74&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) At all trials by a Coast Guard Court, as soon as the court is assembled, the`
  line `names of the presiding officer and members shall be read over to the accused, who shall thereupon be`
  line `asked whether he objects to being tried by any officer sitting on the court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused objects to such officer, his objection and also the reply thereto of the officer`
  line `objected to shall be heard and recorded, and the remaining officers of the court shall, in the absence of the`
  line `challenged officer, decide on the objection.`
  line
  line `(3) If the objection is allowed by one-half or more of the votes of the members entitled to vote, the`
  line `objection shall be allowed, and the member objected to shall retire, and his vacancy may be filled in the`
  line `prescribed manner, by another officer subject to the same right of the accused to object.`
  line
  line `(4) Where no challenge is made, or when a challenge has been made and disallowed, or the place of`
  line `every officer successfully challenged has been filled by another officer to whom no objection is made or`
  line `allowed, the court shall proceed with the trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (3462)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 76
  title `Oaths of member, Law Officer and witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1988, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Every officer" (w.e.f. 31-3-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3462&sectionno=75&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) An oath or affirmation in the prescribed`
  line `manner shall be administered to every member of a Coast Guard Court and to the Law Officer or, as the`
  line `case may be, the officer approved under section 73, before the commencement of the trial.`
  line
  line `(2) ^1`
  line `[Every person] giving evidence before a Coast Guard Court shall be examined after being duly`
  line `sworn or affirmed in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall not apply where the witness is a child under twelve years`
  line `of age and the Coast Guard Court is of opinion that though the witness understands the duty of speaking`
  line `the truth, he does not understand the nature of an oath or affirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (3463)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 77
  title `Voting by members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3463&sectionno=76&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub- sections (2) and (3), every decision`
  line `of a Coast Guard Court shall be passed by an absolute majority of votes; and where there is an equality of`
  line `votes on either the finding or the sentence, the decision shall be in favour of the accused.`
  line
  line `(2) No sentence of death shall be passed by a Coast Guard Court without the concurrence of at least`
  line `two-thirds of the members of the court.`
  line
  line `(3) In matters, other than a challenge or the finding or sentence, the presiding officer shall have a`
  line `casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (3464)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 78
  title `General rule as to evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3464&sectionno=77&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, apply to all proceedings before a Coast Guard Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (3465)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 79
  title `Judicial notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3465&sectionno=78&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `A Coast Guard Court may take judicial notice of any matter within the general`
  line `knowledge of the members as officers of the Coast Guard.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (3466)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 80
  title `Summoning of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3466&sectionno=79&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The convening authority, the presiding officer of a Coast Guard`
  line `Court, the Law Officer or, as the case may be, the officer approved under section 73 or the Commanding`
  line `Officer of the accused person may, by summons under his hand, require the attendance, at a time and`
  line `place to be mentioned in the summons, of any person either to give evidence or to produce any document`
  line `or other thing.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a witness who is subject to this Act, the summons shall be sent to his Commanding`
  line `Officer and such officer shall serve it upon him accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any other witness, the summons shall be sent to the Magistrate within whose`
  line `jurisdiction he may be, or resides, and such Magistrate shall give effect to the summons as if the witness`
  line `were required in the court of such a Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(4) When a witness is required to produce any particular document or other thing in his possession or`
  line `power, the summons shall describe it with reasonable precision.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (3467)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 81
  title `Documents exempted from production.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3467&sectionno=80&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 79 shall be deemed to affect`
  line `the operation of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), or to apply to any`
  line `letter, post card, telegram or other document in the custody of the postal or telegraph authorities.`
  line
  line `(2) If any document in such custody is, in the opinion of any Chief Judicial Magistrate, Chief`
  line `Metropolitan Magistrate, Court of Session or High Court, wanted for the purpose of any Coast Guard`
  line `Court, such Magistrate or Court may require the postal or telegraph authorities, as the case may be, to`
  line `deliver such document to such person as such Magistrate or Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) If any such document is, in the opinion of any other Magistrate or of any Commissioner of Police`
  line `or District Superintendent of Police wanted for any such purpose, he may require the postal or telegraph`
  line `authorities, as the case may be, to cause such search to be made for, and to detain such document pending`
  line `the orders of any such Chief Judicial Magistrate, Chief Metropolitan Magistrate, Court of Session or High`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (3468)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 82
  title `Commissions for examination of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3468&sectionno=81&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of a trial by a Coast`
  line `Guard Court, it appears to the court that the examination of a witness is necessary for the ends of justice,`
  line `and that the attendance of such witness cannot be procured without an amount of delay, expense or`
  line `inconvenience which, in the circumstances of the case, would be unreasonable, such court may address`
  line `the Chief Law Officer in order that a commission to take the evidence of such witness may be issued.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Law Officer may then, if he thinks necessary, issue a commission to any Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class, within the local limits of whose jurisdiction such`
  line `witness resides, to take the evidence of such witness.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate to whom the commission is issued, or, if he is the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate`
  line `or Chief Judicial Magistrate, he or such Metropolitan Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class as`
  line `he appoints in this behalf shall proceed to the place where the witness is, or shall summon the witness`
  line `before him and shall take down his evidence in the same manner, and may, for this purpose, exercise the`
  line `same powers, as in the trials of warrant-cases under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(4) When the witness resides in any place outside India, the commission may be issued in the`
  line `form and manner specified in sub section (3) of section 285 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (3469)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 83
  title `Examination of a witness on commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3469&sectionno=82&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The prosecutor and the accused person in any`
  line `case in which a commission is issued under section 81 may respectively forward any interrogatories in`
  line `writing which the court may think relevant to the issue, and the Magistrate executing the commission`
  line `shall examine the witness upon such interrogatories.`
  line
  line `(2) The prosecutor and the accused person may appear before such Magistrate by counsel, or except`
  line `in the case of an accused person in custody, in person, and may examine, cross-examine and re-examine,`
  line `as the case may be, the said witness.`
  line
  line `(3) After a commission issued under section 81 has been duly executed, it shall be returned together`
  line `with the deposition of the witness examined thereunder to the Chief Law Officer.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of a commission, and deposition returned under sub-section (3), the Chief Law Officer`
  line `shall forward the same to the Coast Guard Court at whose instance the commission was issued or, if such`
  line `court has been dissolved, to any other court convened for the trial of the accused person; and the`
  line `commission, the return thereto and the deposition shall be open to inspection by the prosecutor and the`
  line `accused person, and may, subject to all just exceptions, be read in evidence in the case by either the`
  line `prosecutor or the accused, and shall form part of the proceedings of the court.`
  line
  line `(5) In every case in which a commission is issued under section 81, the trial may be adjourned for a`
  line `specified time reasonably sufficient for the execution and return of the commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (3470)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 84
  title `Alternative findings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3470&sectionno=83&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `If an accused is charged before a Coast Guard Court with one offence and`
  line `it appears in evidence that he committed a different offence, he may be convicted of the offence which he`
  line `is shown to have committed although he was not charged with it.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (3471)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 85
  title `Presumption as to signatures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3471&sectionno=84&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act, any application, certificate,`
  line `warrant, reply or other document purporting to be signed by an officer in the service of the Government`
  line `shall, on production, be presumed to have been duly signed by the person by whom and in the character in`
  line `which it purports to have been signed, until the contrary is shown.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (3472)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 86
  title `Enrolment paper.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3472&sectionno=85&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any enrolment paper purporting to be signed by an enrolling officer`
  line `shall, in proceedings under this Act, be evidence of the person enrolled having given the answers to`
  line `questions which he is therein represented as having given.`
  line
  line `(2) The enrolment of such person may be proved by the production of the original or a copy of his`
  line `enrolment paper purporting to be certified to be a true copy by the officer having the custody of the`
  line `enrolment paper.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (3473)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 87
  title `Presumption as to certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 9 (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3473&sectionno=86&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) A letter, return or other document respecting the`
  line `service of any person in, or the dismissal or discharge of any person from, any unit or ship of the Coast`
  line `Guard, or respecting the circumstances of any person not having served in, or belonged to, any unit or`
  line `ship, if purporting to be signed by or on behalf of the Central Government or the Director-General, or by`
  line `any prescribed officer, shall be evidence of the facts stated in such letter, return or other document.`
  line
  line `(2) A Coast Guard List or Gazette purporting to be published by authority shall be evidence of the`
  line `status and rank of the officers therein mentioned, and of any appointment held by them and of the unit or`
  line `ship of the Coast Guard to which they belong.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a record is made in the books of a ship in pursuance of this Act or any rule or otherwise in`
  line `the discharge of official duties, and purports to be signed by the Commanding Officer or by the officer`
  line `whose duty it is to make such record, such record shall be evidence of the facts therein stated.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of any record in the books of a ship purporting to be certified to be a true copy by the`
  line `officer having custody of such books shall be evidence of such record.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any person subject to this Act is being tried on a charge of desertion or of absence without`
  line `leave, and such person has surrendered himself into the custody of any officer or other person subject to`
  line `this Act or any unit or ship of the Coast Guard, or has been apprehended by such officer or person, a`
  line `certificate purporting to be signed by such officer, or by the Commanding Officer of the unit or ship to`
  line `which such person belongs, as the case may be, and stating the fact, date and place of such surrender or`
  line `apprehension, and the manner in which he was dressed shall be evidence of the matters so stated.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any person subject to this Act is being tried on a charge of desertion or of improperly`
  line `leaving a ship or of absence without leave and such person has surrendered himself into the custody of, or`
  line `has been apprehended by, a police officer not below the rank of an officer in charge of a police station, a`
  line `certificate purporting to be signed by such police officer and stating the fact, date and place of such`
  line `surrender or apprehension and the manner in which he was dressed shall be evidence of the matters so`
  line stated.
  line
  line `(7) Any document purporting to be a report under the hand of a Chemical Examiner or Assistant`
  line `Chemical Examiner to Government ^1`
  line `[or any of the Government scientific experts, namely, the Chief`
  line `Inspector of the Explosives, the Director of the Fingerprint Bureau, the Director, Haffkeine Institute,`
  line `Mumbai, the Director of a Central Forensic Science Laboratory or a State Forensic Science Laboratory`
  line `and the Serologist to the Government] upon any matter or thing duly submitted to him for examination or`
  line `analysis and report, may be used as evidence in any proceeding under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the term "books of a ship" shall include any official book, document or`
  line `list purporting to contain the name or names of persons appointed to the ship.`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (3474)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 88
  title `Evidence of previous convictions and general character.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3474&sectionno=87&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to this`
  line `Act has been convicted by a Coast Guard Court of any offence, such court may inquire into, and receive,`
  line `and record evidence of any previous convictions of such person, either by a Coast Guard Court or by a`
  line `criminal court, or any previous award of punishment under section 57 ^1`
  line `[or section 57A], and may further`
  line `inquire into and record the general character of such person and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Evidence received under this section may be either oral, or in the shape of entries in, or certified`
  line `extracts from, books of Coast Guard Courts or other official records; and it shall not be necessary to give`
  line `notice before trial to the person tried, that evidence as to his previous convictions or character will be`
  line received.
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (3475)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 89
  title `Lunacy of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3475&sectionno=88&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of a trial by a Coast Guard Court, it appears to`
  line `the court that the person charged is by reason of unsoundness of mind incapable of making his defence, or`
  line `that he committed the act alleged but was by reason of unsoundness of mind incapable of knowing the`
  line `nature of the act or knowing that it was wrong or contrary to law, the court shall record a finding`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) The presiding officer of the Coast Guard Court shall forthwith report the case to the convening`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(3) The convening authority to whom the finding of a Coast Guard Court is reported under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall order the accused person to be kept in custody in the prescribed manner and shall`
  line `report the case for the orders of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of a report under sub-section (3), the Central Government may order the accused`
  line `person to be detained in a lunatic asylum or other suitable place of safe custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (3476)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 90
  title `Subsequent fitness of lunatic accused for trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3476&sectionno=89&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Where any accused person, having been found`
  line `by reason of unsoundness of mind to be incapable of making his defence, is in custody or under detention`
  line `under section 88, any officer prescribed in this behalf, may,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such person is in custody under sub-section (3) of section 88, on the report of a medical`
  line `officer that he is capable of making his defence, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person is detained in jail under sub-section (4) of section 88, on a certificate of the`
  line `Inspector-General of Prisons, and if such person is detained in a lunatic asylum under the said`
  line `sub-section, on a certificate of any two or more of the visitors of such asylum and if he is detained in`
  line `any other place under that sub-section, on a certificate of the prescribed authority, that he is capable`
  line `of making his defence,`
  line
  line `take steps to have such person tried by the same or another Coast Guard Court for the offence with which`
  line `he was originally charged, or, if the offence is a civil offence, by a criminal court.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (3477)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 91
  title `Transmission to Central Government of orders under section 89.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3477&sectionno=90&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `A copy of every order`
  line `made by an officer under section 89 for the trial of the accused shall forthwith be sent to the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (3478)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 92
  title `Release of lunatic accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3478&sectionno=91&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Where any person is in custody under sub-section (3) of section 88`
  line `or under detention under sub-section (4) of that section,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such person is in custody under the said sub-section (3), on the report of the medical`
  line `officer, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person is detained under the said sub-section (4), on a certificate from any of the`
  line `authorities mentioned in clause (b) of section 89 that in the judgment of such officer or authority such`
  line `person may be released without danger of his doing injury to himself or to any other person,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may order that such person be released or detained in custody, or transferred to a`
  line `public lunatic asylum if he has not already been sent to such asylum.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (3479)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 93
  title `Delivery of lunatic accused to relatives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3479&sectionno=92&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Where any relative or friend of any person who is in`
  line `custody under sub-section (3) of section 88 or under detention under sub-section (4) of that section`
  line `desires that he should be delivered to his care and custody, the Central Government may, upon`
  line `application by such relative or friend and, on his giving security to the satisfaction of that Government`
  line `that the person delivered shall be properly taken care of, and, prevented from doing injury to himself or to`
  line `any other person, and be produced for the inspection of such officer, and at such times and places, as the`
  line `Central Government may direct, order such person to be delivered to such relative or friend.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (3480)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 94
  title `Order for custody and disposal of property pending trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3480&sectionno=93&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `When any property regarding`
  line `which any offence appears to have been committed, or which appears to have been used for the`
  line `commission of any offence, is produced before a Coast Guard Court during a trial, the court may make`
  line `such order as it thinks fit for the proper custody of such property pending the conclusion of the trial, and`
  line `if the property is subject to speedy or natural decay may, after recording such evidence as it thinks`
  line `necessary, order it to be sold or otherwise disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (3481)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 95
  title `Order for disposal of property regarding which offence is committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3481&sectionno=94&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the`
  line `conclusion of a trial before a Coast Guard Court, an officer not below the rank of a Deputy`
  line `Inspector-General within whose command the trial was held, may make such order as he thinks fit for the`
  line `disposal by destruction, confiscation, delivery to any person claiming to be entitled to possession thereof,`
  line `or otherwise, of any property or document produced before the court or in its custody, or regarding which`
  line `any offence appears to have been committed or which has been used for the commission of any offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any order has been made under sub-section (1) in respect of property regarding which an`
  line `offence appears to have been committed, a copy of such order signed and certified by the authority`
  line `making the same may, whether the trial was held within India or not, be sent to a Magistrate within whose`
  line `jurisdiction such property for the time being is situated, and such Magistrate shall thereupon cause the`
  line `order to be carried out into effect as if it were an order passed by him under the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, the term "property" includes, in the case of property regarding which an offence`
  line `appears to have been committed, not only such property as has been originally in the possession or under.`
  line `the control of any person, but also any property into or for which the same may have been converted or`
  line `exchanged, and anything acquired by such conversion or exchange whether immediately or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (3482)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 96
  title `Powers of Coast Guard Court in relation to proceedings under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3482&sectionno=95&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `Any trial by a`
  line `Coast Guard Court under the provisions of this Act shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Coast Guard Court`
  line `shall be deemed to be a court within the meaning of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (3483)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 97
  title `Form of sentence of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3483&sectionno=96&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `In awarding a sentence of death, a Coast Guard Court shall, in its`
  line `discretion, direct that the offender shall suffer death by being hanged by the neck until he be dead or shall`
  line `suffer death by being shot to death.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (3484)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 98
  title `Interim custody until execution of sentence of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3484&sectionno=97&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `A person sentenced to death may be`
  line `detained in Coast Guard custody or may be removed to a civil prison to be kept in custody until further`
  line `orders are received from the Central Government, the Director-General or the convening authority of the`
  line `Coast Guard Court by which he was sentenced to death or other prescribed officer, and the order of the`
  line `Central Government, the Director-General or the convening authority or such officer shall be sufficient`
  line `warrant for detaining the person in custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (3485)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 99
  title `Execution of sentence of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3485&sectionno=98&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a sentence of death is to be executed, the`
  line `Director-General or the convening authority or the prescribed officer shall give directions as to the time,`
  line `place and manner in which such sentence is to be carried out and the order of such officer or authority in`
  line `the prescribed form shall be sufficient warrant for the execution of such sentence.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be attached to the prescribed form, an order of the Central Government certifying the`
  line `confirmation of the sentence by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (3486)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 100
  title `Commencement of sentence of imprisonment or detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3486&sectionno=99&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is`
  line `sentenced under this Act to imprisonment or detention, the term of the sentence shall be reckoned to`
  line `commence on the date on which the sentence was awarded.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (3487)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 101
  title `Execution of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3487&sectionno=100&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any sentence of imprisonment is`
  line `passed under this Act or whenever any sentence of death is commuted to imprisonment, the presiding`
  line `officer of the Coast Guard Court which passed the sentence or such other officer as may be prescribed`
  line `shall direct that the sentence shall be carried out by confinement in a civil prison.`
  line
  line `(2) When a direction has been made under sub-section (1), the Commanding Officer of the person`
  line `under sentence or such other officer as may be prescribed shall forward a warrant in the prescribed form`
  line `to the officer in charge of the prison in which such person is to be confined and shall arrange for his`
  line `despatch to such prison with the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (3488)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 102
  title `Temporary custody of offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3488&sectionno=101&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Where a sentence of imprisonment is directed to be`
  line `undergone in a civil prison, the offender may be kept in Coast Guard custody or in any other fit place, till`
  line `such time as it is possible to send him to a civil prison.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (3489)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 103
  title `Conveyance of prisoner from place to place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3489&sectionno=102&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `A person under sentence of imprisonment may`
  line `during his conveyance from place to place, or when on board a ship, aircraft or otherwise, be subject to`
  line `such restraint as is necessary for his safe conduct and removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (3490)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 104
  title `Communication of certain orders to prison officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3490&sectionno=103&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `Whenever an order is duly made under`
  line `this Act setting aside or varying any sentence, order or warrant under which any person is confined in a`
  line `civil prison, a warrant in accordance with such order shall be forwarded by the officer making the order or`
  line `his staff officer or such person as may be prescribed, to the officer in charge of the prison in which such`
  line `person is confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (3491)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 105
  title `Execution of Sentence of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3491&sectionno=104&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `When a sentence of fine is imposed by a Coast Guard Court`
  line `under section 53, a copy of such sentence signed and certified by the presiding officer of the court may be`
  line `sent to any Magistrate in India and such Magistrate shall thereupon cause the fine to be recovered in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), as if it were a`
  line `sentence of fine imposed by such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (3492)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 106
  title `Informality or error in the order or warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3492&sectionno=105&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is sentenced to`
  line `imprisonment under this Act, and is undergoing the sentence in any place or manner in which he might be`
  line `confined under a lawful order or warrant in pursuance of this Act, the confinement of such person shall`
  line `not be deemed to be illegal only by reason of any informality or error in, or as respects the order, warrant`
  line `or other document, or the authority by which, or in pursuance whereof such person was brought into, or is`
  line `confined in any such place, and any such order, warrant or document may be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (3493)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 107
  title `Imprisonment or detention of offender already under sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3493&sectionno=106&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a sentence is`
  line `passed by a Coast Guard Court on a person already under sentence either of imprisonment or detention`
  line `passed on him under this Act for a former offence, the court may award a sentence of imprisonment or`
  line `detention for the offence for which he is under trial to commence at the expiration of the sentence of`
  line `imprisonment or detention to which he has been previously sentenced:`
  line
  line `Provided that so much of any term of detention imposed on a person by a sentence in pursuance of`
  line `this section as will prolong the total term of detention beyond two years shall be deemed to be remitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (3494)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 108
  title `Suspension of sentence of imprisonment or detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3494&sectionno=107&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person subject to this`
  line `Act is sentenced to imprisonment or detention, the Central Government, the Director-General, the`
  line `Commanding Officer imposing the sentence or any prescribed officer may suspend the sentence whether`
  line `or not the offender has already been committed to prison or to Coast Guard custody.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority or officer specified in sub-section (1) may, in the case of an offender so sentenced,`
  line `direct that until the orders of such authority or officer have been obtained, the offender shall not be`
  line `committed to prison or to Coast Guard custody.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers conferred by sub-sections (1) and (2) may be exercised in the case of any such`
  line `sentence which has been reduced or commuted.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (3495)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 109
  title `Release on suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3495&sectionno=108&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `Where a sentence is suspended under section 107, the offender shall`
  line `forthwith be released from custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (3496)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 110
  title `Computation of period of suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3496&sectionno=109&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `Any period during which the sentence is under`
  line `suspension shall be reckoned as part of the term of such sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (3497)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 111
  title `Order after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3497&sectionno=110&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `The authority or officer specified in section 107 may, at any time`
  line `while a sentence is suspended, order--`
  line
  line `(a) that the offender be committed to undergo the unexpired portion of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the sentence be remitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (3498)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 112
  title `Reconsideration of case after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3498&sectionno=111&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a sentence has been suspended, the case`
  line `may at any time, and shall at intervals of not more than four months, be reconsidered by the authority or`
  line `officer specified in section 107, or by any officer not below the rank of a Deputy Inspector-General duly`
  line `authorised by the authority or officer specified in section 107.`
  line
  line `(2) Where on such reconsideration by the officer so authorised it appears to him that the conduct of`
  line `offender since his conviction has been such as to justify a remission of the sentence, he shall refer the`
  line `matter to the authority or officer specified in section 107.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (3499)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 113
  title `Fresh sentence after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3499&sectionno=112&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `Where an offender, while a sentence on him is suspended`
  line `under this Act, is sentenced for any other offence, then--`
  line
  line `(a) if the further sentence is also suspended under this Act, the sentence shall run concurrently;`
  line
  line `(b) if the further sentence is for a period of three months or more and is not suspended under this`
  line `Act, the offender shall also be committed to prison or Coast Guard custody for the unexpired portion`
  line `of the previous sentence, but both sentences shall run concurrently; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the further sentence is for a period of less than three months and is not suspended under this`
  line `Act, the offender shall be so committed on that sentence only, and the previous sentence shall, subject`
  line `to any order which may be passed under section 110 or section 111 continue to be suspended.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (3500)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 114
  title `Scope of power of suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3500&sectionno=113&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `The powers conferred by sections 107 and 110 shall be in`
  line `addition to, and not in derogation of, the power of mitigation, remission and commutation.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (3501)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 115
  title `Effect of suspension and remission on dismissal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3501&sectionno=114&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in addition to any other`
  line `sentence, the punishment of dismissal has been awarded under this Act and such other sentence is`
  line `suspended under section 107, then, such dismissal shall not take effect until so ordered by the authority or`
  line `officer specified in section 107.`
  line
  line `(2) If such other sentence is remitted under section 110, the punishment of dismissal shall also be`
  line remitted.
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (3502)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 116
  title `Appointment of Chief Law Officer and Law Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3502&sectionno=115&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government, a Chief Law Officer and as many Law Officers as the Central Government may`
  line `deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as Chief Law Officer unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India; and`
  line
  line `(b) has for at least ten years held a judicial office in the territory of India; or`
  line
  line `(c) has for at least ten years been an advocate of a High Court or two or more such Courts in`
  line `succession:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if it is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do`
  line `in the exigencies of service, relax, for reasons to be recorded in writing, the qualification specified in`
  line `clause (b) or clause (c) in respect of any person.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as Law Officer unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India, and`
  line
  line `(b) is qualified for enrolment as an advocate of a High Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) in computing the period during which a person has been an advocate of a High Court, there`
  line `shall be included any period during which the person has held a judicial office after he became an`
  line advocate;
  line
  line `(b) the expression "judicial office" shall be deemed to include the post of Law Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (3503)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 117
  title `Functions of Chief Law Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3503&sectionno=116&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Chief Law Officer to perform`
  line `such duties of a legal and judicial character pertaining to the Coast Guard as may, from time to time, be`
  line `referred or assigned to him by the Central Government or the Director-General, and to discharge the`
  line `functions conferred on him by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions of the Chief Law Officer shall, in his absence or otherwise, be performed by such`
  line `Law Officer as may be designated in this behalf by the Director-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (3504)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 118
  title `Judicial review by the Chief Law Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3504&sectionno=117&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) All proceedings of trials by Coast Guard`
  line `Courts shall be reviewed by the Chief Law Officer either on his own motion or on application made`
  line `to him within the prescribed time by any person aggrieved by any sentence or finding, and the Chief Law`
  line `Officer shall transmit the report of such review together with such recommendations as may appear`
  line `to him just and proper to the Director-General for his consideration and for such action as the`
  line `Director-General may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person aggrieved has made an application under sub-section (1), the Chief Law Officer`
  line `may, if the circumstances of the case so require, give him an opportunity of being heard either in person`
  line `or through a legal practitioner or an officer of the Coast Guard.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (3505)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 119
  title `Consideration by the Director-General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3505&sectionno=118&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the report and recommendations, if`
  line `any, under section 117, the Director-General shall in all cases of sentences of death, and in all cases`
  line `where the Coast Guard Court is convened by the Central Government, and may, in other cases, transmit`
  line `the proceedings and the report to the Central Government together with such recommendations as he may`
  line `deem fit to make.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in section 117 or this section shall authorise the Chief Law Officer or the`
  line `Director-General to make any recommendation for setting aside, or the Central Government to set aside,`
  line `an order of acquittal passed under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (3506)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 120
  title `Petitions to Central Government or Director-General against findings and sentences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3506&sectionno=119&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person subject to this Act who considers himself aggrieved by a finding or sentence of any Coast Guard`
  line `Court may present a petition to the Central Government or to the Director-General, and the Central`
  line `Government or the Director-General, as the case may be, may pass such orders thereon as it or he may`
  line `think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (3507)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 121
  title `Powers of Central Government and Director-General in respect of findings and sentences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3507&sectionno=120&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person is tried under the provisions of this Act, the Central Government or`
  line `the Director-General may, in the case of a conviction,--`
  line
  line `(a) set aside the finding and sentence and acquit or discharge the accused or order him to be`
  line `re-tried; or`
  line
  line `(b) alter the finding without modifying the sentence if such sentence may be legally passed on the`
  line `altered finding; or`
  line
  line `(c) with or without altering the finding, reduce the sentence or commute the punishment awarded`
  line `for any punishment inferior in scale; or`
  line
  line `(d) either with or without conditions, pardon the person or remit the whole or any part of the`
  line `punishment awarded; or`
  line
  line `(e) with or without conditions release the person on parole:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sentence of imprisonment shall not be commuted for a sentence of detention for a`
  line `term exceeding the term of imprisonment awarded:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this sub-section shall authorise the Central Government or the`
  line `Director-General to enhance the sentence.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sentence modified under the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be carried into execution as if`
  line `it had been originally passed.`
  line
  line `(3) If any condition on which a person has been pardoned or has been released on parole or a`
  line `punishment has been remitted is in the opinion of the authority which granted the pardon, release or`
  line `remission not fulfilled, such authority may cancel the pardon or release or remission and thereupon the`
  line `sentence awarded shall be carried into effect as if such pardon, release or remission had not been granted:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a person sentenced to imprisonment or detention, such person shall`
  line `undergo only the unexpired portion of the sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (3508)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 122
  title `Powers and duties conferrable and imposable on members of the Coast Guard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3508&sectionno=121&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, direct that, subject`
  line `to such conditions and limitations, and within the local limits of such inland area adjoining the coast of`
  line `India, as may be specified in the order, any member of the Coast Guard may,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the purpose of prevention of any offence punishable under the Passport (Entry into India)`
  line `Act, 1920 (34 of 1920), the Emigration Act, 1922 (7 of 1922), the Registration of Foreigners`
  line `Act, 1939 (16 of 1939), the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946), the Merchant Shipping Act,`
  line `1958 (44 of 1958), the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), the Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967), the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), or the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf,`
  line `Exclusive Economic Zone and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), or of any cognizable`
  line `offence punishable under any other Central Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for the purpose of apprehending any person who has committed any offence referred to in`
  line `clause (i),`
  line
  line `exercise or discharge such of the powers or duties under that Act or any other Central Act as may be`
  line `specified in the said order, being the powers and duties which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `an officer of the corresponding or lower rank is by that or such other Act empowered to exercise or`
  line `discharge for the said purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, direct,`
  line `with the concurrence of the State Government concerned, that any of the powers or duties which may be`
  line `exercised or discharged under a State Act by a police officer may, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, and within the local limits of such inland area adjoining the coast of India, as may be`
  line `specified in the order, be exercised or discharged by a member of the Coast Guard who, in the opinion of`
  line `the Central Government, holds a corresponding or higher rank.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that, subject to such conditions and limitations, and within the local limits of such area in any maritime`
  line `zone of India, as may be specified in the order, any member of the Coast Guard may,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the purpose of prevention of any offence punishable under any enactment which extends`
  line `for the time being to such area; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for the purpose of apprehending any person who has committed any offence referred to in`
  line `clause (i),`
  line
  line `exercise or discharge such of the powers or duties under that enactment, as may be specified in the said`
  line `order, being the powers and duties which, in the opinion of the Central Government, an officer of the`
  line `corresponding or lower rank is by that enactment empowered to exercise or discharge for the said`
  line purposes.
  line
  line `(4) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (3509)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 123
  title `Protection for acts of members of the Coast Guard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3509&sectionno=122&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any suit or proceeding against`
  line `any member of the Coast Guard for any act done by him in pursuance of a warrant or order of a`
  line `competent authority, it shall be lawful for him to plead that such act was done by him under the authority`
  line `of such warrant or order.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such plea may be proved by the production of the warrant or order directing the act, and if it`
  line `is so proved, the member of the Coast Guard shall thereupon be discharged from liability in respect of the`
  line `act so done by him, notwithstanding any defect in the jurisdiction of the authority which issued such`
  line `warrant or order.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any legal`
  line `proceeding (whether civil or criminal) which may lawfully be brought against any member of the Coast`
  line `Guard for anything done or intended to be done under the powers conferred by, or in pursuance of any`
  line `provision of this Act or the rules, shall be commenced within three months after the act complained of`
  line `was committed and not otherwise, and notice in writing of such proceeding and of the cause thereof shall`
  line `be given to the defendant or his superior officer at least one month before the commencement of such`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (3510)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 124
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2002, s. 11 (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203&sectionId=3510&sectionno=123&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00016_197830_1517807325203
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for the`
  line `purpose of carrying into effect the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for,--`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution, governance, command and discipline of the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(b) the enrolment of persons to the Coast Guard and the recruitment of other members of the`
  line `Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions of service (including service privileges and deductions from pay and`
  line `allowances) of members of the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(d) the rank, precedence, powers of command and authority of the officers, subordinate officers`
  line `and other enrolled persons;`
  line
  line `(e) the removal, retirement, release or discharge from the service of officers, subordinate officers`
  line `and other enrolled persons;`
  line
  line `(f) the purposes and other matters required to be prescribed under section 13;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(fa) the manner in which proceedings may be initiated under section 57A;]`
  line
  line `(g) the additional matters in respect of which the Coast Guard may undertake measures in the`
  line `performance of its functions;`
  line
  line `(h) the convening, constitution, adjournment, dissolution and sittings of Coast Guard Courts, the`
  line `procedure to be observed in trials by such courts, the persons by whom an accused may be defended`
  line `in such trials and the appearance of such persons thereat;`
  line
  line `(i) the forms of orders to be made under the provisions of this Act relating to Coast Guard Courts`
  line `and the awards and infliction of death, imprisonment and detention;`
  line
  line `(j) the carrying into effect of sentences of Coast Guard Courts;`
  line
  line `(k) any matter necessary for the purpose of carrying this Act into execution, as far as it relates to`
  line `the investigation, arrest, custody, trial and punishment of offences triable or punishable under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(l) the procedure relating to the exercise of powers under section 120;`
  line
  line `(m) the ceremonials to be observed and marks of respect to be paid in the Coast Guard;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed or in respect of which this Act makes no`
  line `provision or makes insufficient provision and provision is, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `necessary for the proper implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
